works.description: Germany’s MK-Group Holding has announced that the company will be distributing an all-electric variant of the Fiat 500 at a cost of 23,900 euros, which doesn’t include batteries as they will be provided at a price of 150 euros per month, which also includes a flat-rate fee for electricity. Manufactured by Swedish company EVadapt, the electric Fiat 500, dubbed CARe 500, has already been made available.
